So yeah, league is racially diverse. And it has pirate, ninja, robot, zombie, kungfu chicks too so...

Remember that PROMOTING DIVERSITY is not the same as NOT BEING RACIST. While it is good to have black characters, diversity means a lot more than adding more black heroes so that you are not labelled as racist. A LOT of american series have a very hamfisted approach to diversity because they are legally obliged to have a diverse cast and thus make really poor black characters AND make him handicapped, gay, ugly, nerdy, jewish or transgender (*cough cough Unique from Glee, Stevie from Malcolm in the Middle, Angela Pearly-Gates Montenegro cough cough) just so that the rest of the cast can just be blond, rich and white.

Valuing a culturally diverse hero in League and indeed, valuing a cultural hero in real life means respecting his/her deeds, his cultural heritage, manerisms and language and wrapping it up in a snazzy package because he/she is cool. It's harder to make a cool black character because the expectations are higher and probably because  most writers are white males and it's downright insulting and racist to make a hero whoose only definining trait is that he is black. Therefore I'd rather have only 1 badass Samuel Lee Jackson type character done well than having a multitude of Steve Urkels and Jar jar binks. 

